content.text: JavaScript Window Navigator
The Navigator Object
The navigator object contains information about the visitor's browser.
content.html: The navigator object contains information about the visitor's browser.

content.text: It can be written with or without the window prefix like:
content.html: It can be written with or without the window prefix like:

content.text: windows.navigator or just navigator
content.html: windows.navigator or just navigator

content.text: Browser Cookies
The cookieEnabled property returns true if cookies are enabled, otherwise false:
content.html: The cookieEnabled property returns true if cookies are enabled, otherwise false:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
"cookiesEnabled is " + navigator.cookieEnabled;
</script>

content.text: The Browser Language
The language property returns the browser's language:
content.html: The language property returns the browser's language:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = navigator.language;
</script>

content.text: Is The Browser Online?
The onLine property returns true if the browser is online:
content.html: The onLine property returns true if the browser is online:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = navigator.onLine;
</script>

content.text: Browser Application Name
The appName property returns the application name of the browser:
content.html: The appName property returns the application name of the browser:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
"navigator.appName is " + navigator.appName;
</script>

content.text: Warning
This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.
content.html: This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.

content.text: Most browsers (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari) returns Netscape as appName .
content.html: Most browsers (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari) returns Netscape as appName.

content.text: Browser Application Code Name
The appCodeName property returns the application code name of the browser:
content.html: The appCodeName property returns the application code name of the browser:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
"navigator.appCodeName is " + navigator.appCodeName;
</script>

content.text: Warning
This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.
content.html: This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.

content.text: Most browsers (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari) returns Mozilla as appCodeName .
content.html: Most browsers (Chrome, Edge, Firefox, Safari) returns Mozilla as appCodeName.

content.text: The Browser Engine
The product property returns the product name of the browser engine:
content.html: The product property returns the product name of the browser engine:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML =
"navigator.product is " + navigator.product;
</script>

content.text: Warning
This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.
content.html: This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.

content.text: Most browsers returns Gecko as product.
content.html: Most browsers returns Gecko as product.

content.text: The Browser Version
The appVersion property returns version information about the browser:
content.html: The appVersion property returns version information about the browser:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = navigator.appVersion;
</script>

content.text: Warning
This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.
content.html: This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.

content.text: Do not rely on appVersion to return the correct browser version.
content.html: Do not rely on appVersion to return the correct browser version.

content.text: The Browser Agent
The userAgent property returns the user-agent header sent by the browser to the server:
content.html: The userAgent property returns the user-agent header sent by the browser to the server:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = navigator.userAgent;
</script>

content.text: Warning
The information from the navigator object can often be misleading.
content.html: The information from the navigator object can often be misleading.

content.text: The navigator object should not be used to detect browser versions because:
content.html: The navigator object should not be used to detect browser versions because:

content.text: The Browser Platform
The platform property returns the browser platform (operating system):
content.html: The platform property returns the browser platform (operating system):

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = navigator.platform;
</script>

content.text: Warning
This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.
content.html: This property is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.

content.text: Do not rely on platform to return the correct browser platform in all browsers.
content.html: Do not rely on platform to return the correct browser platform in all browsers.

content.text: Is Java Enabled?
The javaEnabled() method returns true if Java is enabled:
content.html: The javaEnabled() method returns true if Java is enabled:

content.code_html:
<p id="demo"></p>

<script>
document.getElementById("demo").innerHTML = navigator.javaEnabled();
</script>

content.text: Warning
This method is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.
content.html: This method is removed (deprecated) in the latest web standard.

content.text: javaEnabled() always returns false .
content.html: javaEnabled() always returns false.
